Notes: This was my favorite brunch spot!! It's on Haight st, and I went here almost every weekend. Try their open faced egg sandwich or their french toast!
They're famous for their chicken + waffles! Also, they have an in-house dj that plays some really solid blues.
Fancy overpriced toast? Yeah, go here at least once. It's some of the best toast you'll ever have.
This place in the Mission is opened by a chef that won so many awards. Try The Rebel Within (an egg encased by a muffin)!
In the Mission, this is one of the best bakeries in the city.
Another solid brunch spot in the Haight.
The place for real connoisseurs (which I am def not since I don't drink coffee.) Jack Dorsey swears by this place. Also, the affogato is really, really good.
Super bougie coffee shop (think wood panels and warehouse setting) but the coffee (and affogato) is alright (and overpriced)!
Pricey (~$20/pizza) but really good! Recommend getting the avocado toast and splitting a pizza with someone.
Super amazing authentic Italian pizza in the Mission! Try the burrata and any of their pizzas - you can't go wrong.

Literally the best ramen you'll ever have! It only opens for dinner and takes no reservations so get there right when it opens. You'll still probably have to wait 20min-2h, but it's 110% worth. I went at least 3x in my 3 months in SF.
Also one of the best ramen spots in the city! Mensho > Nojo imho though
Also a really great ramen spot, but can't compare to Nojo or Mensho.
Quality Thai food! Reserve in advance, esp. on weekends
A super delicious Italian restaurant in North Beach

You have to try their famous donut burger (or chicken + waffles) at least once! This place is extremely extra but you have to go. It's carnival themed and the guest book they give you to sign is super fun!
A super famous burrito place in the Mission
High class Mexican food in the Panhandle
I love this sushi place/bar! Try the hamachi truffle with their sakes!
Solid Vietnamese food. Try the chicken ramen or garlic noodles. Also, this was n8 and Joe's favorite place last summer and you know how n8 feels about pho.
New orleans style food! Quality comfort food.
Great burger place in Cole Valley! The avocado burger is top.
Japanese street food! Seriously solid skewers.
Expensive, date night sort of place that I happily tried by myself. Pretty good.
I haven't personally been here, but it was recommended to me by someone who is great at food.
Really, really good Greek food. I like their chicken salad and fries with garlic Greek yogurt sauce.
They have delicious floats and handmade ice cream! The coconut almond vegan ice cream is literally better than most non-vegan ice creams.
Some of the best ice cream in SF! Using nitrogen to freeze it, the ice cream is really creamy. They do cool flavor combos such as red pepper ice cream with honey
Solid if you're in the area, but not my fave
Froyo!
They serve boba in glass bottles that you get to keep! The nutella one is my fave.
It's p solid at boba
